7.theory:
# Array dalam JavaScript

Array adalah struktur data untuk menyimpan kumpulan nilai dalam satu variabel.

## 1. Membuat Array
```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
let mixed = [1, "hello", true, null];
```

## 2. Mengakses Elemen Array
```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];

console.log(fruits[0]); // "apple" (indeks 0)
console.log(fruits[1]); // "banana" (indeks 1)
console.log(fruits.length); // 3 (panjang array)
```

## 3. Array Methods - Manipulasi
```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana"];

// push - tambah di akhir
fruits.push("orange"); // ["apple", "banana", "orange"]

// pop - hapus dari akhir
let last = fruits.pop(); // "orange", fruits = ["apple", "banana"]

// unshift - tambah di awal
fruits.unshift("grape"); // ["grape", "apple", "banana"]

// shift - hapus dari awal
let first = fruits.shift(); // "grape", fruits = ["apple", "banana"]
```

## 4. Array Methods - Iterasi
```javascript
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// forEach
numbers.forEach(num => console.log(num));

// map - transformasi array
let doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2); // [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]

// filter - filtering array
let even = numbers.filter(num => num % 2 === 0); // [2, 4]

// find - mencari elemen
let found = numbers.find(num => num > 3); // 4
```

## 5. Array Methods - Lainnya
```javascript
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// reduce - akumulasi
let sum = numbers.reduce((total, num) => total + num, 0); // 15

// some & every
let hasEven = numbers.some(num => num % 2 === 0); // true
let allPositive = numbers.every(num => num > 0); // true

// sort
let sorted = [3, 1, 4, 2].sort((a, b) => a - b); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Contoh Praktis:
```javascript
let students = [
  { name: "Alice", score: 85 },
  { name: "Bob", score: 92 },
  { name: "Charlie", score: 78 }
];

// Cari student dengan score tertinggi
let topStudent = students.reduce((best, student) => 
  student.score > best.score ? student : best
);

// Hitung rata-rata score
let average = students.reduce((sum, student) => 
  sum + student.score, 0) / students.length;

console.log(topStudent.name); // "Bob"
console.log(average); // 85
```

