11.theory:
# Higher-Order Functions

Higher-order functions adalah fungsi yang menerima fungsi sebagai parameter atau mengembalikan fungsi.

## 1. Map, Filter, Reduce - Review Lanjutan
```javascript
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// Map - transform each element
let squared = numbers.map(x => x * x); // [1, 4, 9, 16, 25]

// Filter - select elements
let even = numbers.filter(x => x % 2 === 0); // [2, 4]

// Reduce - accumulate values
let sum = numbers.reduce((acc, curr) => acc + curr, 0); // 15
```

## 2. Creating Custom Higher-Order Functions
```javascript
// Fungsi yang menerima function sebagai parameter
function processArray(arr, processor) {
  let result = [];
  for (let item of arr) {
    result.push(processor(item));
  }
  return result;
}

let numbers = [1, 2, 3];
let doubled = processArray(numbers, x => x * 2); // [2, 4, 6]
let strings = processArray(numbers, x => `Number: ${x}`);
// ["Number: 1", "Number: 2", "Number: 3"]
```

## 3. Function Composition
```javascript
// Menggabungkan multiple functions
const compose = (...functions) => input => 
  functions.reduceRight((acc, fn) => fn(acc), input);

const add5 = x => x + 5;
const multiply3 = x => x * 3;
const subtract2 = x => x - 2;

const complexOperation = compose(subtract2, multiply3, add5);
console.log(complexOperation(10)); // (10 + 5) * 3 - 2 = 43
```

## 4. Currying
```javascript
// Transform function dengan multiple arguments menjadi sequence of functions
const multiply = (a, b, c) => a * b * c;

// Curried version
const curriedMultiply = a => b => c => a * b * c;

console.log(multiply(2, 3, 4)); // 24
console.log(curriedMultiply(2)(3)(4)); // 24

// Partial application
const multiplyBy2 = curriedMultiply(2);
const multiplyBy2And3 = multiplyBy2(3);
console.log(multiplyBy2And3(4)); // 24
```

## 5. Closure dalam Higher-Order Functions
```javascript
function createCounter() {
  let count = 0;

  return {
    increment: () => ++count,
    decrement: () => --count,
    getCount: () => count
  };
}

const counter = createCounter();
console.log(counter.increment()); // 1
console.log(counter.increment()); // 2
console.log(counter.getCount()); // 2
```

