# Pemrograman Asynchronous

JavaScript adalah single-threaded, tetapi bisa menangani operasi asynchronous menggunakan callbacks, promises, dan async/await.

## 1. Callback Functions
```javascript
// Synchronous callback
function processNumber(num, callback) {
  return callback(num * 2);
}

let result = processNumber(5, x => x + 10);
console.log(result); // 20

// Asynchronous callback (simulasi)
function fetchData(callback) {
  setTimeout(() => {
    callback("Data received!");
  }, 1000);
}

fetchData(data => {
  console.log(data); // "Data received!" (setelah 1 detik)
});
```

## 2. Callback Hell (Pyramid of Doom)
```javascript
// Masalah dengan nested callbacks
function getUserData(userId, callback) {
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Got user data");
    callback({ id: userId, name: "John" });
  }, 1000);
}

function getPosts(user, callback) {
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Got user posts");
    callback(["Post 1", "Post 2"]);
  }, 1000);
}

function getComments(posts, callback) {
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Got comments");
    callback(["Comment 1", "Comment 2"]);
  }, 1000);
}

// Callback hell
getUserData(1, user => {
  getPosts(user, posts => {
    getComments(posts, comments => {
      console.log("All data:", { user, posts, comments });
    });
  });
});
```

## 3. Introduction to Promises
```javascript
// Membuat Promise
const fetchData = () => {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    setTimeout(() => {
      const success = Math.random() > 0.3;
      if (success) {
        resolve("Data fetched successfully!");
      } else {
        reject("Failed to fetch data");
      }
    }, 1000);
  });
};

// Menggunakan Promise
fetchData()
  .then(data => {
    console.log("Success:", data);
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.log("Error:", error);
  });
```

## 4. Promise Chaining
```javascript
const getUser = (userId) => {
  return new Promise(resolve => {
    setTimeout(() => resolve({ id: userId, name: "John" }), 500);
  });
};

const getPosts = (user) => {
  return new Promise(resolve => {
    setTimeout(() => resolve(["Post 1", "Post 2"]), 500);
  });
};

const getComments = (posts) => {
  return new Promise(resolve => {
    setTimeout(() => resolve(["Comment 1", "Comment 2"]), 500);
  });
};

// Promise chaining (solusi untuk callback hell)
getUser(1)
  .then(user => {
    console.log("User:", user);
    return getPosts(user);
  })
  .then(posts => {
    console.log("Posts:", posts);
    return getComments(posts);
  })
  .then(comments => {
    console.log("Comments:", comments);
    console.log("All operations completed!");
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.error("Error:", error);
  });
```

## 5. Promise Static Methods
```javascript
// Promise.all - menunggu semua promise selesai
const promise1 = Promise.resolve(3);
const promise2 = 42;
const promise3 = new Promise((resolve) => {
  setTimeout(resolve, 100, "foo");
});

Promise.all([promise1, promise2, promise3])
  .then(values => {
    console.log(values); // [3, 42, "foo"]
  });

// Promise.race - mengambil yang pertama selesai
const fastPromise = new Promise(resolve => 
  setTimeout(resolve, 100, "Fast")
);
const slowPromise = new Promise(resolve => 
  setTimeout(resolve, 500, "Slow")
);

Promise.race([fastPromise, slowPromise])
  .then(result => {
    console.log(result); // "Fast"
  });
```

