# ES6 Modules: Import dan Export

ES6 Modules memungkinkan kita memisahkan kode ke dalam file yang berbeda dan mengatur dependencies dengan baik.

## 1. Named Exports
```javascript
// math.js - Multiple named exports
export const PI = 3.14159;

export function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}

export function multiply(a, b) {
  return a * b;
}

// Atau export di akhir file
const subtract = (a, b) => a - b;
const divide = (a, b) => a / b;

export { subtract, divide };
```

## 2. Default Export
```javascript
// calculator.js - Single default export
class Calculator {
  constructor() {
    this.result = 0;
  }

  add(x) {
    this.result += x;
    return this;
  }

  getResult() {
    return this.result;
  }
}

export default Calculator;
```

## 3. Import Statements
```javascript
// Import named exports
import { PI, add, multiply } from './math.js';

// Import dengan alias
import { add as tambah, multiply as kali } from './math.js';

// Import semua named exports sebagai object
import * as mathUtils from './math.js';

// Import default export
import Calculator from './calculator.js';

// Mixed imports
import Calculator, { PI } from './modules.js';
```

## 4. Dynamic Imports
```javascript
// Dynamic import (lazy loading)
async function loadModule(moduleName) {
  try {
    const module = await import(`./modules/${moduleName}.js`);
    return module;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Failed to load module ${moduleName}:`, error);
    return null;
  }
}

// Menggunakan dynamic import
loadModule('advancedMath')
  .then(mathModule => {
    if (mathModule) {
      console.log(mathModule.calculateAdvanced(5));
    }
  });
```

