# Event Handling dalam JavaScript

Events memungkinkan JavaScript merespons interaksi user seperti clicks, keyboard input, form submissions, dll.

## 1. Basic Event Listeners
```javascript
// Method 1: addEventListener (recommended)
const button = document.getElementById('myButton');
button.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
  console.log('Button clicked!', event);
});

// Method 2: Inline event handlers (less recommended)
<button onclick="handleClick()">Click me</button>

// Method 3: Event handler properties
button.onclick = function() {
  console.log('Button clicked!');
};
```

## 2. Common Event Types
```javascript
// Click events
element.addEventListener('click', handleClick);

// Form events
form.addEventListener('submit', handleSubmit);
input.addEventListener('input', handleInput);
input.addEventListener('change', handleChange);

// Keyboard events
document.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
document.addEventListener('keyup', handleKeyUp);

// Mouse events
element.addEventListener('mouseover', handleMouseOver);
element.addEventListener('mouseout', handleMouseOut);

// Window events
window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);
window.addEventListener('load', handleLoad);
```

## 3. Event Object dan Methods
```javascript
function handleClick(event) {
  // Prevent default behavior (e.g., form submission, link navigation)
  event.preventDefault();

  // Stop event bubbling
  event.stopPropagation();

  // Event properties
  console.log('Target:', event.target); // Element yang triggered event
  console.log('Current target:', event.currentTarget); // Element dengan event listener
  console.log('Event type:', event.type);

  // Mouse event properties
  console.log('Coordinates:', event.clientX, event.clientY);

  // Keyboard event properties
  console.log('Key pressed:', event.key);
  console.log('Key code:', event.code);
}
```

## 4. Event Delegation
```javascript
// Instead of adding listeners to each item
// Add one listener to parent
const list = document.getElementById('myList');

list.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
  // Check if clicked element is a list item
  if (event.target.tagName === 'LI') {
    console.log('List item clicked:', event.target.textContent);
    event.target.classList.toggle('selected');
  }

  // Or check for specific class
  if (event.target.classList.contains('delete-btn')) {
    event.target.parentElement.remove();
  }
});
